		<div class="long">
			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,2266116)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-2266116">
																		
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/thedeadlymoose" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(732274); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=732274&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610204701" alt="thedeadlymoose" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=732274)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/thedeadlymoose" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(732274); return false;" >thedeadlymoose</a></span> <span class="odate time_1428441765 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">07 Apr 2015 21:22</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2266116">
									

<p>This is a part of <a href="/resurrection">Resurrection</a>. It was not properly entered as such because&#8230; likely, because we confused L0rdDeath, so he didn't know the process for adding it.</p>
<p><strong>However,</strong> this <em>was</em> edited with the assistance of the other Resurrection writers and approved for inclusion on the hub (anyone can write a story for Resurrection, it's only hub inclusion that needs approval).</p>
<p>Even though it is in the negatives, it is fully part of the canon until &amp; unless it gets deleted. As such, I'm going to go ahead and add it to hub now.</p>
<p>(EDITx3: Wow, go moose. He actually did add it to the hub, just did it in a funky way.)</p>
<p>As I mentioned on IRC, this does border on cheese for me, and parts are imperfect, but I enjoy the characterization and world-building enough that it works for me. I really like the Huntsmen conceptually, and Foxx walks the 'cheese line' <em>just</em> enough that he works for me. The emphasis of his home life helps with this in particular.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Nitpick</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>A small side note: Skitter Marshall doesn't match Resurrection's 'compatibility requirement' for matching accepted general mainline canon (such as it exists) for <em>the</em> Mister Marshall (see: <a href="/thank-you-for-your-time">Thank You For Your Time</a>, <a href="/acquisitions-hub">Acquisitions Hub</a>, and linked works on Acquisitions), but as I said on IRC, this could simply be another family member, with Jeremy Marshall being <em>the</em> Marshall, and Skitter has no reason to say otherwise. And I like that character quite a bit, actually.</p>
<p>I would <em>suggest</em> that Foxx have a thought that it might or might not be <em>the</em> Marshall, but that's up to L0rdDeath.</p>
<p><strong>EDIT:</strong> Oh gods, I forgot about <a href="/wills-and-ways-hub">Wills And Ways Hub</a>. Okay, yeah, then we definitely can go with multiple Marshalls with no concerns. And if the tale survives, let's probably link that tale for the reference :]</p>
</div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
</div>
</div>
<p>I enjoy this, regardless of whether it bites the dust. +1'd. :)</p>
<p>EDIT x2: Also, note, though, just because something is part of Resurrection, doesn't mean it can't be extensively edited even if future articles have already been created building off of it. This is one reason we have a group &#8212; to take care of these sorts of snarls. Feedback away.</p>

							</div>

								
