			<div class="content" id="post-content-2266245">
									

<p>Like I had said in chat, I like the first half (since <em>that</em> portion was the entire article back then). I wish to talk about the second half, after the item swap.</p>
<ul>
<li>I was initially iffy with the SCP documentation. It was referred to as &quot;he&quot; in-article for that portion. Of course, it ended off just when it is about to describe the anomaly. Now I wonder what does &quot;Moss Heart? mean?</li>
<li>The idea of Huntsmen is intriguing. Not sure if other SCPs/Tales did it, but it could be an angle to look at for MC&amp;D concepts.</li>
<li>Now if I'm not mistaken, Foxx's current allegiance is to the Foundation. Or will he toe the line between the 2 organisations?</li>
</ul>
<p>I was initially sceptical of this work, but the idea of a (possibly) anomalous person leading a <em>relatively</em> normal life (with a family to boot) is something we don't get all that often here. You could explore on Foxx's relationship with his daughter (I would imagine it to be scenarios where the triad father refuses to let their kid know of their business).</p>

							</div>

								
